  ;; ── GPIO Assignment table ────────────────────────────────────────
  (text "ESP32-WROVER-E GPIO ASSIGNMENT (v1.1)\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nIO0   → BOOT button at power-on (pull-up R2 10k)    [DUAL]\n        → I2S_MCLK output after boot (12.288MHz MCLK)\nIO2   → ENCODER_A  (pull-up 10k, 10nF debounce)\nIO4   → ENCODER_B  (pull-up 10k, 10nF debounce)\nIO5   → ENCODER_SW (pull-up 10k)\nIO12  → LCD_DC                              strapping: keep LOW at boot\nIO13  → LCD_BL (PWM LEDC ch0)\nIO14  → LCD_RST\nIO15  → SPI_CLK  (VSPI SCLK)\nIO18  → I2S_BCLK  (ES7243E + MAX98357A shared)\nIO19  → I2S_LRCK  (WS)\nIO21  → I2S_DIN   (data from ES7243E SDOUT)\nIO22  → I2C_SCL   (SI4732 + ES7243E)\nIO23  → I2C_SDA   (SI4732 + ES7243E)\nIO25  → SPI_MOSI  (VSPI MOSI)\nIO26  → LCD_CS\nIO27  → SI_RESET  (active-low to SI4732)\nIO32  → BT_LED    [FIXED: was AUDIO_MUTE (now via I2C GPO1 property)]\nIO33  → AMP_SD    (MAX98357A SD_MODE, HIGH=play, LOW=mute)\nIO34  → [UNUSED - input only, leave floating or pull to GND]\nEN    → RESET via R1 10k pull-up + C_EN 100nF + SW1\nTXD0  → CP2102N RXD\nRXD0  → CP2102N TXD\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nWARNING: IO34-39 are input-only → cannot drive LEDs or outputs\nWARNING: IO16/IO17 used internally by PSRAM → do NOT route externally\nNOTE: IO0 MCLK requires firmware: i2s_ll_set_mclk_src(I2S_NUM_0, I2S_MCLK_SIGNAL_APLL)\n      Set APLL to 12.288MHz or 11.2896MHz before starting I2S driver\n\n[FIX LOG v1.1 - 2026-04-28]\n  BUG-03: BT_LED assigned to IO34 (input-only) → cannot output\n  FIX-03: IO32 reassigned to BT_LED; SI4732 mute uses I2C property 0x0102\n  BUG-01: ES7243E MCLK floating → PLL fail\n  FIX-01: IO0 added as I2S_MCLK output (dual-function: BOOT at reset, MCLK at run)"
    (at 220 90)
    (effects (font (size 1.7 1.7)) (justify left))
  )
)
